		<h2>POSTGRADUATE STUDY AT THE DDS</h2><p>The Digital Design Studio seeks to develop creative thinking through a sound understanding of digital visualization technologies.  To find out more about our postgraduate opportunities, please follow the links on the website or download information <a href="\downloads\dds\dds flyer.pdf" target="new window">here</a> (PDF).</p><p>The <b>MPhil 2D/3D Motion Graphics</b> is a multidisciplinary two-year programme designed to enable graduates from a wide range of backgrounds to carry forward their ideas and ambitions through an animation programme. Thus, scientists, designers, philosophers, artists, astrophysicists, cartographers, architects, programmers, photographers, to name some, have already studied at the DDS.  The course is focused on a final year individual programme of study proposed and executed by the student. </p><p>For more information about this programme please follow the link on the left.</p><p>The GSA is now the second largest art and design research community in the UK, generating new knowledge through creative practice and scholarship in art, design and architecture.  The Digital Design Studio plays a major role in our research activity and details on PhD opportunties can be found on the Research Opportunties link on the left.</p><h2>OUR GRADUATES</h2><p>The MPhil 2D/3D Motion Graphics enjoys a 90% employment rate. Our graduates occupy positions with companies such as Sony, Ragdoll Productions, DMA Design, Digital Animations, Viz, and Peugeot Citroen. Other graduates have established their own companies in the field of digital animation while others have taken academic positions in the Higher Education sector.</p>
	

	

	

	

	

	

	
	
	
	
	


	
	







